    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nIf the values cmdheight=0, laststatus=0, and ui2 are enabled, then after executing the command (displaying the message), a status line artifact appears (screenshots).\n\ncmdheight=0, laststatus=0, ui2 enabled\n<img width=\"1054\" height=\"215\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b2fd7671-5829-4d5b-9dbd-952aa794f675\" />\ncmdheight=0, laststatus=0, ui2 disabled\n<img width=\"1054\" height=\"215\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/91c222bd-80f6-4ed5-8e7f-8d98bbd6e3a1\" />\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nSet options and execute command(\":w\" for example):\nvim.opt.cmdheight = 0\nvim.opt.laststatus = 0\nrequire(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable({})\n\nSet options and execute command(\":w\" for example) without ui2:\nvim.opt.cmdheight = 0\nvim.opt.laststatus = 0\n \n```\n\n## Expected behavior\nNo status line artifact when cmdheight=0, laststatus=0, ui2\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-12 ga358b9be64` neovim/neovim@a358b9be64\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.19.11-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: ghostty 1.3.1-arch1\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-ghostty`\n- Installation: src\n\n",
